Style types for zithril TUI framework\n// Re-exports and extends rich_zig's Style with zithril-specific conveniences\n\nconst std = @import(\"std\");\npub const rich_zig = @import(\"rich_zig\");\n\n/// Re-export rich_zig's Color for convenience.\npub const Color = rich_zig.Color;\n\n/// Re-export rich_zig's StyleAttribute for convenience.\npub const StyleAttribute = rich_zig.StyleAttribute;\n\n/// Style represents visual attributes for text cells.\n///\n/// Wraps rich_zig.Style with zithril-specific conveniences.\n/// Supports:\n/// - Foreground and background colors (via Color)\n/// - Text attributes: bold, italic, underline, dim, blink, reverse, strikethrough\n/// - Method chaining for building styles\n/// - Merging styles via patch() (called combine() in rich_zig)\n///\n/// Example:\n/// ```\n/// const highlight = Style.init().bold().fg(.yellow).bg(.blue);\n/// const merged = base_style.patch(highlight);\n/// ```\npub const Style = struct {\n    inner: rich_zig.Style,\n\n    /// Empty style with all defaults.\n    pub const empty: Style = .{ .inner = rich_zig.Style.empty };\n\n    /// Initialize an empty style.\n    pub fn init() Style {\n        return empty;\n    }\n\n    /// Set foreground color.\n    pub fn fg(self: Style, c: Color) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.fg(c) };\n    }\n\n    /// Set foreground color (alias for fg).\n    pub fn foreground(self: Style, c: Color) Style {\n        return self.fg(c);\n    }\n\n    /// Set background color.\n    pub fn bg(self: Style, c: Color) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.bg(c) };\n    }\n\n    /// Set background color (alias for bg).\n    pub fn background(self: Style, c: Color) Style {\n        return self.bg(c);\n    }\n\n    /// Enable bold.\n    pub fn bold(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.bold() };\n    }\n\n    /// Disable bold.\n    pub fn notBold(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.notBold() };\n    }\n\n    /// Enable italic.\n    pub fn italic(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.italic() };\n    }\n\n    /// Disable italic.\n    pub fn notItalic(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.notItalic() };\n    }\n\n    /// Enable underline.\n    pub fn underline(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.underline() };\n    }\n\n    /// Disable underline.\n    pub fn notUnderline(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.notUnderline() };\n    }\n\n    /// Enable dim.\n    pub fn dim(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.dim() };\n    }\n\n    /// Disable dim.\n    pub fn notDim(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.notDim() };\n    }\n\n    /// Enable blink.\n    pub fn blink(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.blink() };\n    }\n\n    /// Disable blink.\n    pub fn notBlink(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.notBlink() };\n    }\n\n    /// Enable reverse video.\n    pub fn reverse(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.reverse() };\n    }\n\n    /// Disable reverse video.\n    pub fn notReverse(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.notReverse() };\n    }\n\n    /// Enable strikethrough.\n    pub fn strikethrough(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.strikethrough() };\n    }\n\n    /// Disable strikethrough.\n    pub fn notStrikethrough(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.notStrike() };\n    }\n\n    /// Enable strikethrough (alias).\n    pub fn strike(self: Style) Style {\n        return self.strikethrough();\n    }\n\n    /// Merge another style on top of this one.\n    /// Non-default values in `other` override values in `self`.\n    pub fn patch(self: Style, other: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.combine(other.inner) };\n    }\n\n    /// Merge another style on top of this one (alias for patch).\n    pub fn combine(self: Style, other: Style) Style {\n        return self.patch(other);\n    }\n\n    /// Check if style has a specific attribute enabled.\n    pub fn hasAttribute(self: Style, attr: StyleAttribute) bool {\n        return self.inner.hasAttribute(attr);\n    }\n\n    /// Check if this style has no attributes or colors set.\n    pub fn isEmpty(self: Style) bool {\n        return self.inner.isEmpty();\n    }\n\n    /// Check equality with another style.\n    pub fn eql(self: Style, other: Style) bool {\n        return self.inner.eql(other.inner);\n    }\n\n    /// Access the underlying rich_zig style for advanced operations.\n    pub fn toRichStyle(self: Style) rich_zig.Style {\n        return self.inner;\n    }\n\n    /// Create from a rich_zig style.\n    pub fn fromRichStyle(rich_style: rich_zig.Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = rich_style };\n    }\n};\n\n// ============================================================\n// SANITY TESTS - Basic functionality\n// ============================================================\n\ntest \"sanity: Style.init creates empty style\" {\n    const style = Style.init();\n    try std.testing.expect(style.isEmpty());\n}\n\ntest \"sanity: Style.empty is empty\" {\n    try std.testing.expect(Style.empty.isEmpty());\n}\n\ntest \"sanity: Style with attribute is not empty\" {\n    const style = Style.init().bold();\n    try std.testing.expect(!style.isEmpty());\n}\n\ntest \"sanity: Style with color is not empty\" {\n    const style = Style.init().fg(.red);\n    try std.testing.expect(!style.isEmpty());\n}\n\n// ============================================================\n// BEHAVIOR TESTS - Attribute chaining and patching\n// ============================================================\n\ntest \"behavior: Style attribute chaining\" {\n    const style = Style.init().bold().italic().underline().fg(.green);\n    try std.testing.expect(style.hasAttribute(.bold));\n    try std.testing.expect(style.hasAttribute(.italic));\n    try std.testing.expect(style.hasAttribute(.underline));\n}\n\ntest \"behavior: Style.patch merges styles\" {\n    const base = Style.init().bold().fg(.red);\n    const overlay = Style.init().italic().fg(.blue);\n\n    const merged = base.patch(overlay);\n    try std.testing.expect(merged.hasAttribute(.bold));\n    try std.testing.expect(merged.hasAttribute(.italic));\n}\n\ntest \"behavior: Style.patch overlay wins for conflicts\" {\n    const base = Style.init().bold().fg(.red);\n    const overlay = Style.init().notBold().fg(.blue);\n\n    const merged = base.patch(overlay);\n    try std.testing.expect(!merged.hasAttribute(.bold));\n}\n\ntest \"behavior: Style equality\" {\n    const s1 = Style.init().bold().fg(.red);\n    const s2 = Style.init().bold().fg(.red);\n    const s3 = Style.init().bold().fg(.blue);\n\n    try std.testing.expect(s1.eql(s2));\n    try std.testing.expect(!s1.eql(s3));\n}\n\ntest \"behavior: Style all attributes\" {\n    const style = Style.init()\n        .bold()\n        .italic()\n        .underline()\n        .dim()\n        .blink()\n        .reverse()\n        .strikethrough();\n\n    try std.testing.expect(style.hasAttribute(.bold));\n    try std.testing.expect(style.hasAttribute(.italic));\n    try std.testing.expect(style.hasAttribute(.underline));\n    try std.testing.expect(style.hasAttribute(.dim));\n    try std.testing.expect(style.hasAttribute(.blink));\n    try std.testing.expect(style.hasAttribute(.reverse));\n    try std.testing.expect(style.hasAttribute(.strike));\n}\n\ntest \"behavior: Style disable attributes\" {\n    const style = Style.init().bold().notBold();\n    try std.testing.expect(!style.hasAttribute(.bold));\n}\n\n// ============================================================\n// INTEGRATION TESTS - rich_zig interop\n// ============================================================\n\ntest \"integration: Style to/from rich_zig\" {\n    const zithril_style = Style.init().bold().fg(.red);\n    const rich_style = zithril_style.toRichStyle();\n\n    try std.testing.expect(rich_style.hasAttribute(.bold));\n\n    const back = Style.fromRichStyle(rich_style);\n    try std.testing.expect(back.eql(zithril_style));\n}\n","numLines":267,"startLine":1,"totalLines":267}}}

};\n    pub const bright_magenta: Color = .{ .color_type = .standard, .number = 13 };\n    pub const bright_cyan: Color = .{ .color_type = .standard, .number = 14 };\n    pub const bright_white: Color = .{ .color_type = .standard, .number = 15 };\n\n    pub fn fromRgb(r: u8, g: u8, b: u8) Color {\n        return .{\n            .color_type = .truecolor,\n            .triplet = .{ .r = r, .g = g, .b = b },\n        };\n    }\n\n    pub fn fromHex(hex_str: []const u8) !Color {\n        const start: usize = if (hex_str.len > 0 and hex_str[0] == '#') 1 else 0;\n        if (hex_str.len - start != 6) return error.InvalidHexColor;\n\n        const r = std.fmt.parseInt(u8, hex_str[start..][0..2], 16) catch return error.InvalidHexColor;\n        const g = std.fmt.parseInt(u8, hex_str[start..][2..4], 16) catch return error.InvalidHexColor;\n        const b = std.fmt.parseInt(u8, hex_str[start..][4..6], 16) catch return error.InvalidHexColor;\n\n        return fromRgb(r, g, b);\n    }\n\n    pub fn from256(number: u8) Color {\n        return .{\n            .color_type = .eight_bit,\n            .number = number,\n        };\n    }\n\n    pub fn downgrade(self: Color, target: ColorSystem) Color {\n        return switch (self.color_type) {\n            .default => self,\n            .standard => self,\n            .eight_bit => switch (target) {\n                .standard => self.toStandard(),\n                .eight_bit, .truecolor => self,\n            },\n            .truecolor => switch (target) {\n                .standard => self.toStandard(),\n                .eight_bit => self.to256(),\n                .truecolor => self,\n            },\n        };\n    }\n\n    fn toStandard(self: Color) Color {\n        const triplet = self.getTriplet() orelse return Color.white;\n\n        var best_index: u8 = 0;\n        var best_distance: i32 = std.math.maxInt(i32);\n\n        for (standard_color_triplets, 0..) |std_color, i| {\n            const dr: i32 = @as(i32, triplet.r) - @as(i32, std_color.r);\n            const dg: i32 = @as(i32, triplet.g) - @as(i32, std_color.g);\n            const db: i32 = @as(i32, triplet.b) - @as(i32, std_color.b);\n            const distance = dr * dr + dg * dg + db * db;\n\n            if (distance < best_distance) {\n                best_distance = distance;\n                best_index = @intCast(i);\n            }\n        }\n\n        return .{ .color_type = .standard, .number = best_index };\n    }\n\n    fn to256(self: Color) Color {\n        const triplet = self.triplet orelse return self;\n        const number = rgbTo256(triplet.r, triplet.g, triplet.b);\n        return Color.from256(number);\n    }\n\n    pub fn getTriplet(self: Color) ?ColorTriplet {\n        if (self.triplet) |t| return t;\n\n        // For 256 colors, convert back to RGB approximation\n        if (self.color_type == .eight_bit) {\n            if (self.number) |n| {\n                return tripletFrom256(n);\n            }\n        }\n\n        // For standard colors, return approximate RGB values\n        if (self.color_type == .standard) {\n            if (self.number) |n| {\n                if (n < standard_color_triplets.len) {\n                    return standard_color_triplets[n];\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        return null;\n    }\n\n    pub fn getAnsiCodes(self: Color, foreground: bool, writer: anytype) !void {\n        const base: u8 = if (foreground) 30 else 40;\n\n        switch (self.color_type) {\n            .default => try writer.print(\"{d}\", .{if (foreground) @as(u8, 39) else @as(u8, 49)}),\n            .standard => {\n                const num = self.number orelse return;\n                if (num < 8) {\n                    try writer.print(\"{d}\", .{base + num});\n                } else {\n                    try writer.print(\"{d}\", .{base + 60 + num - 8});\n                }\n            },\n            .eight_bit => {\n                const num = self.number orelse return;\n                try writer.print(\"{d};5;{d}\", .{ if (foreground) @as(u8, 38) else @as(u8, 48), num });\n            },\n            .truecolor => {\n                const t = self.triplet orelse return;\n                try writer.print(\"{d};2;{d};{d};{d}\", .{\n                    if (foreground) @as(u8, 38) else @as(u8, 48),\n                    t.r,\n                    t.g,\n                    t.b,\n                });\n            },\n        }\n    }\n\n    pub fn eql(self: Color, other: Color) bool {\n        if (self.color_type != other.color_type) return false;\n        if (self.number != other.number) return false;\n        if (self.triplet == null and other.triplet == null) return true;\n        if (self.triplet == null or other.triplet == null) return false;\n        return self.triplet.?.eql(other.triplet.?);\n    }\n\n    pub fn paletteToRgb(n: u8) ColorTriplet {\n        return tripletFrom256(n);\n    }\n};\n\npub fn rgbTo256(r: u8, g: u8, b: u8) u8 {\n    // Check for grayscale\n    if (r == g and g == b) {\n        if (r < 8) return 16;\n        if (r > 248) return 231;\n        return @as(u8, @intFromFloat((@as(f32, @floatFromInt(r)) - 8.0) / 247.0 * 24.0)) + 232;\n    }\n\n    // Use 6x6x6 color cube (colors 16-231)\n    const ri: u8 = @intFromFloat(@round(@as(f32, @floatFromInt(r)) / 255.0 * 5.0));\n    const gi: u8 = @intFromFloat(@round(@as(f32, @floatFromInt(g)) / 255.0 * 5.0));\n    const bi: u8 = @intFromFloat(@round(@as(f32, @floatFromInt(b)) / 255.0 * 5.0));\n    return 16 + 36 * ri + 6 * gi + bi;\n}\n\n// RGB values for the 16 standard terminal colors\nconst standard_color_triplets = [16]ColorTriplet{\n    .{ .r = 0, .g = 0, .b = 0 }, // black\n    .{ .r = 128, .g = 0, .b = 0 }, // red\n    .{ .r = 0, .g = 128, .b = 0 }, // green\n    .{ .r = 128, .g = 128, .b = 0 }, // yellow\n    .{ .r = 0, .g = 0, .b = 128 }, // blue\n    .{ .r = 128, .g = 0, .b = 128 }, // magenta\n    .{ .r = 0, .g = 128, .b = 128 }, // cyan\n    .{ .r = 192, .g = 192, .b = 192 }, // white\n    .{ .r = 128, .g = 128, .b = 128 }, // bright_black\n    .{ .r = 255, .g = 0, .b = 0 }, // bright_red\n    .{ .r = 0, .g = 255, .b = 0 }, // bright_green\n    .{ .r = 255, .g = 255, .b = 0 }, // bright_yellow\n    .{ .r = 0, .g = 0, .b = 255 }, // bright_blue\n    .{ .r = 255, .g = 0, .b = 255 }, // bright_magenta\n    .{ .r = 0, .g = 255, .b = 255 }, // bright_cyan\n    .{ .r = 255, .g = 255, .b = 255 }, // bright_white\n};\n\npub fn tripletFrom256(n: u8) ColorTriplet {\n    if (n < 16) {\n        return standard_color_triplets[n];\n    } else if (n < 232) {\n        // 6x6x6 color cube\n        const cube_index = n - 16;\n        const ri = cube_index / 36;\n        const gi = (cube_index % 36) / 6;\n        const bi = cube_index % 6;\n        return .{\n            .r = if (ri > 0) @as(u8, @intCast(ri * 40 + 55)) else 0,\n            .g = if (gi > 0) @as(u8, @intCast(gi * 40 + 55)) else 0,\n            .b = if (bi > 0) @as(u8, @intCast(bi * 40 + 55)) else 0,\n        };\n    } else {\n        // Grayscale (232-255)\n        const gray = @as(u8, @intCast((n - 232) * 10 + 8));\n        return .{ .r = gray, .g = gray, .b = gray };\n    }\n}\n\n// Named color lookup table for parsing\npub const named_colors = std.StaticStringMap(Color).initComptime(.{\n    .{ \"default\", Color.default },\n    .{ \"black\", Color.black },\n    .{ \"red\", Color.red },\n    .{ \"green\", Color.green },\n    .{ \"yellow\", Color.yellow },\n    .{ \"blue\", Color.blue },\n    .{ \"magenta\", Color.magenta },\n    .{ \"cyan\", Color.cyan },\n    .{ \"white\", Color.white },\n    .{ \"bright_black\", Color.bright_black },\n    .{ \"bright_red\", Color.bright_red },\n    .{ \"bright_green\", Color.bright_green },\n    .{ \"bright_yellow\", Color.bright_yellow },\n    .{ \"bright_blue\", Color.bright_blue },\n    .{ \"bright_magenta\", Color.bright_magenta },\n    .{ \"bright_cyan\", Color.bright_cyan },\n    .{ \"bright_white\", Color.bright_white },\n    .{ \"grey\", Color.bright_black },\n    .{ \"gray\", Color.bright_black },\n});\n\n// Tests\ntest \"ColorTriplet.hex\" {\n    const triplet = ColorTriplet{ .r = 255, .g = 128, .b = 0 };\n    try std.testing.expectEqualStrings(\"#ff8000\", &triplet.hex());\n}\n\ntest \"ColorTriplet.blend\" {\n    const c1 = ColorTriplet{ .r = 0, .g = 0, .b = 0 };\n    const c2 = ColorTriplet{ .r = 255, .g = 255, .b = 255 };\n\n    const mid = ColorTriplet.blend(c1, c2, 0.5);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u8, 127), mid.r);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u8, 127), mid.g);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u8, 127), mid.b);\n\n    const start = ColorTriplet.blend(c1, c2, 0.0);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u8, 0), start.r);\n\n    const end = ColorTriplet.blend(c1, c2, 1.0);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u8, 255), end.r);\n}\n\ntest \"Color.fromHex valid\" {\n    const c1 = try Color.fromHex(\"#ff0000\");\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(ColorType.truecolor, c1.color_type);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u8, 255), c1.triplet.?.r);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u8, 0), c1.triplet.?.g);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u8, 0), c1.triplet.?.b);\n\n    const c2 = try Color.fromHex(\"00ff00\");\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u8, 0), c2.triplet.?.r);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u8, 255), c2.triplet.?.g);\n\n    const c3 = try Color.fromHex(\"#abcdef\");\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u8, 0xab), c3.triplet.?.r);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u8, 0xcd), c3.triplet.?.g);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u8, 0xef), c3.triplet.?.b);\n}\n\ntest \"Color.fromHex invalid\" {\n    try std.testing.expectError(error.InvalidHexColor, Color.fromHex(\"#ff00\"));\n    try std.testing.expectError(error.InvalidHexColor, Color.fromHex(\"ff\"));\n    try std.testing.expectError(error.InvalidHexColor, Color.fromHex(\"#gggggg\"));\n}\n\ntest \"Color.downgrade truecolor to 256\" {\n    const truecolor = Color.fromRgb(255, 0, 0);\n    const downgraded = truecolor.downgrade(.eight_bit);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(ColorType.eight_bit, downgraded.color_type);\n    try std.testing.expect(downgraded.number != null);\n}\n\ntest \"Color.downgrade truecolor to standard\" {\n    const truecolor = Color.fromRgb(255, 0, 0);\n    const downgraded = truecolor.downgrade(.standard);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(ColorType.standard, downgraded.color_type);\n    // Should map to red (1) or bright_red (9)\n    try std.testing.expect(downgraded.number.? == 9 or downgraded.number.? == 1);\n}\n\ntest \"Color.downgrade standard stays standard\" {\n    const standard = Color.red;\n    const downgraded = standard.downgrade(.standard);\n    try std.testing.expect(standard.eql(downgraded));\n}\n\ntest \"Color.getAnsiCodes\" {\n    var buf: [64]u8 = undefined;\n    var stream = std.io.fixedBufferStream(&buf);\n    const writer = stream.writer();\n\n    // Default foreground\n    try Color.default.getAnsiCodes(true, writer);\n    try std.testing.expectEqualStrings(\"39\", stream.getWritten());\n\n    stream.reset();\n\n    // Standard red foreground\n    try Color.red.getAnsiCodes(true, writer);\n    try std.testing.expectEqualStrings(\"31\", stream.getWritten());\n\n    stream.reset();\n\n    // Standard red background\n    try Color.red.getAnsiCodes(false, writer);\n    try std.testing.expectEqualStrings(\"41\", stream.getWritten());\n\n    stream.reset();\n\n    // Bright red foreground (number 9)\n    try Color.bright_red.getAnsiCodes(true, writer);\n    try std.testing.expectEqualStrings(\"91\", stream.getWritten());\n\n    stream.reset();\n\n    // 256 color\n    try Color.from256(196).getAnsiCodes(true, writer);\n    try std.testing.expectEqualStrings(\"38;5;196\", stream.getWritten());\n\n    stream.reset();\n\n    // Truecolor\n    try Color.fromRgb(255, 128, 64).getAnsiCodes(true, writer);\n    try std.testing.expectEqualStrings(\"38;2;255;128;64\", stream.getWritten());\n}\n\ntest \"rgbTo256 grayscale\" {\n    // Pure black\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u8, 16), rgbTo256(0, 0, 0));\n    // Pure white\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u8, 231), rgbTo256(255, 255, 255));\n    // Mid gray\n    const mid_gray = try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u8, 46), pure_green);\n\n    // Pure blue should be near color 21 (0,0,5 in cube)\n    const pure_blue = rgbTo256(0, 0, 255);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u8, 21), pure_blue);\n}\n\ntest \"ColorSystem.supports\" {\n    try std.testing.expect(ColorSystem.truecolor.supports(.truecolor));\n    try for convenience.\npub const Color = rich_zig.Color;\n\n/// Re-export rich_zig's StyleAttribute for convenience.\npub const StyleAttribute = rich_zig.StyleAttribute;\n\n/// Style represents visual highlight = Style.init().bold().fg(.yellow).bg(.blue);\n/// const merged = base_style.patch(highlight);\n/// ```\npub const Style = struct {\n    inner: rich_zig.Style,\n\n    /// Empty style with all color.\n    pub fn fg(self: Style, c: Color) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.fg(c) };\n    }\n\n    /// Set foreground color (alias for fg).\n    pub fn foreground(self: Style, c: Color) Style {\n        return self.fg(c);\n    }\n\n    /// Set background color.\n    pub fn bg(self: Style, c: Color) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.bg(c) };\n    }\n\n    /// Set background color (alias for bg).\n    pub fn background(self: Style, c: Color) Style {\n        return self.bg(c);\n    }\n\n    /// Enable bold.\n    pub fn bold(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.bold() };\n    }\n\n    /// Disable bold.\n    pub fn notBold(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.notBold() };\n    }\n\n    /// Enable italic.\n    pub fn italic(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.italic() };\n    }\n\n    /// Disable italic.\n    pub fn notItalic(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.notItalic() };\n    }\n\n    /// Enable underline.\n    pub fn underline(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.underline() };\n    }\n\n    /// Disable underline.\n    pub fn notUnderline(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.notUnderline() };\n    }\n\n    /// Enable dim.\n    pub fn dim(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.dim() };\n    }\n\n    /// Disable dim.\n    pub fn notDim(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.notDim() };\n    }\n\n    /// Enable blink.\n    pub fn blink(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.blink() };\n    }\n\n    /// Disable blink.\n    pub fn notBlink(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.notBlink() };\n    }\n\n    /// Enable reverse video.\n    pub fn reverse(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.reverse() };\n    }\n\n    /// Disable reverse video.\n    pub fn notReverse(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.notReverse() };\n    }\n\n    /// Enable strikethrough.\n    pub fn strikethrough(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.strikethrough() };\n    }\n\n    /// Disable strikethrough.\n    pub fn notStrikethrough(self: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.notStrike() };\n    }\n\n    /// Enable strikethrough (alias).\n    pub fn strike(self: Style) Style {\n        return self.strikethrough();\n    }\n\n    /// Merge another style on top of this one.\n    /// Non-default values in `other` override values in `self`.\n    pub fn patch(self: Style, other: Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = self.inner.combine(other.inner) };\n    }\n\n    /// Merge another style on top of this one self.inner.eql(other.inner);\n    }\n\n    /// Access the underlying rich_zig style for advanced operations.\n    pub fn toRichStyle(self: Style) rich_zig.Style {\n        return self.inner;\n    }\n\n    /// Create from a rich_zig style.\n    pub fn fromRichStyle(rich_style: rich_zig.Style) Style {\n        return .{ .inner = rich_style };\n    }\n};\n\n// Coordinates increase right and down.\npub const Rect = struct {\n    x: u16,\n    y: u16,\n    width: u16,\n    height: u16,\n\n    pub fn init(x: u16, y: u16, width: u16, height: u16) Rect {\n        return .{ .x = x, .y = y, .width = width, .height = height };\n    }\n\n    /// Returns a new Rect inset by `margin` on all sides.\n    /// Uses saturating subtraction to prevent underflow.\n    /// Position shifts inward; dimensions shrink by 2*margin (or to zero).\n    pub fn inner(self: Rect, margin: u16) Rect {\n        const double_margin = @as(u32, margin) * 2;\n\n        return .{\n            .x = self.x +| margin,\n            .y = self.y +| margin,\n            .width = if (double_margin >= self.width) 0 else self.width - @as(u16, @intCast(double_margin)),\n            .height = if (double_margin >= self.height) 0 else self.height - @as(u16, @intCast(double_margin)),\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Returns area (width * height) as u32 to prevent overflow.\n    pub fn area(self: Rect) u32 {\n        return @as(u32, self.width) * @as(u32, self.height);\n    }\n\n    /// Returns true if rect has zero area.\n    pub fn isEmpty(self: Rect) bool {\n        return self.width == 0 or self.height == 0;\n    }\n\n    /// Clamp a point to be within this rect (inclusive of boundaries).\n    /// Returns the closest point inside the rect.\n    pub fn clamp(self: Rect, x: u16, y: u16) Position {\n        const max_x = self.x +| (self.width -| 1);\n        const max_y = self.y +| (self.height -| 1);\n\n        return .{\n            .x = std.math.clamp(x, self.x, max_x),\n            .y = std.math.clamp(y, self.y, max_y),\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Returns the right edge x coordinate (exclusive).\n    pub fn right(self: Rect) u16 {\n        return self.x +| self.width;\n    }\n\n    /// Returns the bottom edge y coordinate (exclusive).\n    pub fn bottom(self: Rect) u16 {\n        return self.y +| self.height;\n    }\n\n    /// Returns true if the given point is within this rect (inclusive).\n    pub fn contains(self: Rect, x: u16, y: u16) bool {\n        return x >= self.x and\n            x < self.right() and\n            y >= self.y and\n            y < self.bottom();\n    }\n};\n\n// ============================================================\n// SANITY TESTS - Basic functionality\n// std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 0), inner_rect.height);\n}\n\ntest \"behavior: Rect.clamp constrains point to boundaries\" {\n    const rect = Rect.init(10, 20, 100, 50);\n\n    const inside = {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-5-20251101","id":"msg_01HvbgXEtkzNFLiSk6hhxjbL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01TfSHDQE4nKjBMwsZBYatJT","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/hotschmoe/zithril/src/layout.zig","content":"// Layout types for zithril TUI framework\n// Constraint-based layout system inspired by ratatui\n\nconst std = @import(\"std\");\n\n/// Direction for layout: how children are arranged.\npub const Direction = enum {\n    horizontal,\n    vertical,\n};\n\n/// Constraints describe how space should be allocated among layout children.\n///\n/// The constraint solver allocates space in this order:\n/// 1. Fixed constraints (length): Allocate exact requested size\n/// 2. Minimum constraints (min): Allocate at least requested size\n/// 3. Maximum constraints (max): Allocate at most requested size\n/// 4. Ratio constraints (ratio): Allocate fraction of total space\n/// 5. Flex constraints (flex): Distribute remaining space proportionally\n///\n/// When space is insufficient:\n/// - Fixed/min constraints take priority\n/// - Flex items shrink to zero before fixed items shrink\n/// - No negative sizes (saturating arithmetic)\npub const Constraint = union(enum) {\n    /// Exactly n cells.\n    length: u16,\n\n    /// At least n cells.\n    min: u16,\n\n    /// At most n cells.\n    max: u16,\n\n    /// Fraction of available space (numerator, denominator).\n    /// Example: ratio(1, 3) means 1/3 of available space.\n    ratio: Ratio,\n\n    /// Proportional share (like CSS flex-grow).\n    /// flex(1) and flex(1) = 50/50 split\n    /// flex(1) and flex(2) = 33/67 split\n    flex: u16,\n\n    pub const Ratio = struct {\n        num: u16,\n        den: u16,\n    };\n\n    /// Create a length constraint (exactly n cells).\n    pub fn length(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .length = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a minimum constraint (at least n cells).\n    pub fn min(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .min = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a maximum constraint (at most n cells).\n    pub fn max(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .max = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a ratio constraint (num/den of available space).\n    pub fn ratio(num: u16, den: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .ratio = .{ .num = num, .den = den } };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a flex constraint (proportional share).\n    pub fn flex(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .flex = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Apply this constraint to resolve a concrete size given available space.\n    /// Returns the size this constraint requests, which may exceed available space.\n    /// The caller is responsible for ensuring the total doesn't exceed available.\n    pub fn apply(self: Constraint, available: u16) u16 {\n        return switch (self) {\n            .length => |n| n,\n            .min => |n| n,\n            .max => |n| @min(n, available),\n            .ratio => |r| blk: {\n                if (r.den == 0) break :blk 0;\n                const result = (@as(u32, available) * @as(u32, r.num)) / @as(u32, r.den);\n                break :blk @intCast(@min(result, available));\n            },\n            .flex => available,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Check if two constraints are equal.\n    pub fn eql(self: Constraint, other: Constraint) bool {\n        return switch (self) {\n            .length => |n| other == .length and other.length == n,\n            .min => |n| other == .min and other.min == n,\n            .max => |n| other == .max and other.max == n,\n            .ratio => |r| other == .ratio and other.ratio.num == r.num and other.ratio.den == r.den,\n            .flex => |n| other == .flex and other.flex == n,\n        };\n    }\n};\n\n// ============================================================\n// SANITY TESTS - Basic functionality\n// ============================================================\n\ntest \"sanity: Constraint.length creates correct constraint\" {\n    const c = Constraint.length(10);\n    try std.testing.expect(c == .length);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 10), c.length);\n}\n\ntest \"sanity: Constraint.min creates correct constraint\" {\n    const c = Constraint.min(20);\n    try std.testing.expect(c == .min);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 20), c.min);\n}\n\ntest \"sanity: Constraint.max creates correct constraint\" {\n    const c = Constraint.max(30);\n    try std.testing.expect(c == .max);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 30), c.max);\n}\n\ntest \"sanity: Constraint.ratio creates correct constraint\" {\n    const c = Constraint.ratio(1, 3);\n    try std.testing.expect(c == .ratio);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 1), c.ratio.num);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 3), c.ratio.den);\n}\n\ntest \"sanity: Constraint.flex creates correct constraint\" {\n    const c = Constraint.flex(2);\n    try std.testing.expect(c == .flex);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 2), c.flex);\n}\n\ntest \"sanity: Direction enum values\" {\n    try std.testing.expect(@intFromEnum(Direction.horizontal) != @intFromEnum(Direction.vertical));\n}\n\n// ============================================================\n// BEHAVIOR TESTS - Constraint application\n// ============================================================\n\ntest \"behavior: Constraint.length.apply returns exact size\" {\n    const c = Constraint.length(50);\n    try Fixed constraints (length): Allocate exact requested size\n/// 2. Minimum constraints (min): Allocate at least requested size\n/// 3. Maximum constraints (max): Allocate at most requested size\n/// 4. Ratio constraints (ratio): Allocate fraction of total space\n/// 5. Flex constraints (flex): Distribute remaining space proportionally\n///\n/// When space is insufficient:\n/// - Fixed/min constraints take priority\n/// - Flex items shrink to zero before fixed items shrink\n/// - No negative sizes (saturating arithmetic)\npub const Constraint = union(enum) {\n    /// Exactly n cells.\n    length: u16,\n\n    /// At least n cells.\n    min: u16,\n\n    /// At most n cells.\n    max: u16,\n\n    /// Fraction of available space (numerator, denominator).\n    /// Example: ratio(1, 3) means 1/3 of available space.\n    ratio: Ratio,\n\n    /// Proportional share (like CSS flex-grow).\n    /// flex(1) and flex(1) = 50/50 split\n    /// flex(1) and flex(2) = 33/67 split\n    flex: u16,\n\n    pub const Ratio = struct {\n        num: u16,\n        den: u16,\n    };\n\n    /// Create a length constraint (exactly n cells).\n    pub fn length(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .length = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a minimum constraint (at least n cells).\n    pub fn min(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .min = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a maximum constraint (at most n cells).\n    pub fn max(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .max = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a ratio constraint (num/den of available space).\n    pub fn ratio(num: u16, den: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .ratio = .{ .num = num, .den = den } };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a flex constraint (proportional share).\n    pub fn flex(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .flex = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Apply this constraint to resolve a concrete size given available space.\n    /// Returns the size this constraint requests, which may exceed available space.\n    /// The caller is responsible for ensuring the total doesn't exceed available.\n    pub fn apply(self: Constraint, available: u16) u16 {\n        return switch (self) {\n            .length => |n| n,\n            .min => |n| n,\n            .max => |n| @min(n, available),\n n,\n        };\n    }\n};\n\n// ============================================================\n// SANITY TESTS - Basic functionality\n// Fixed constraints (length): Allocate exact requested size\n/// 2. Minimum constraints (min): Allocate at least requested size\n/// 3. Maximum constraints (max): Allocate at most requested size\n/// 4. Ratio constraints (ratio): Allocate fraction of total space\n/// 5. Flex constraints (flex): Distribute remaining space proportionally\n///\n/// When space is insufficient:\n/// - Fixed/min constraints take priority\n/// - Flex items shrink to zero before fixed items shrink\n/// - No negative sizes (saturating arithmetic)\npub const Constraint = union(enum) {\n    /// Exactly n cells.\n    length: u16,\n\n    /// At least n cells.\n    min: u16,\n\n    /// At most n cells.\n    max: u16,\n\n    /// Fraction of available space (numerator, denominator).\n    /// Example: ratio(1, 3) means 1/3 of available space.\n    ratio: Ratio,\n\n    /// Proportional share (like CSS flex-grow).\n    /// flex(1) and flex(1) = 50/50 split\n    /// flex(1) and flex(2) = 33/67 split\n    flex: u16,\n\n    pub const Ratio = struct {\n        num: u16,\n        den: u16,\n    };\n\n    /// Create a length constraint (exactly n cells).\n    pub fn len(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .length = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a minimum constraint (at least n cells).\n    pub fn minSize(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .min = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a maximum constraint (at most n cells).\n    pub fn maxSize(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .max = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a ratio constraint (num/den of available space).\n    pub fn fractional(num: u16, den: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .ratio = .{ .num = num, .den = den } };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a flex constraint (proportional share).\n    pub fn flexible(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .flex = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Apply this constraint to resolve a concrete size given available space.\n    /// Returns the size this constraint requests, which may exceed available space.\n    /// The caller is responsible for ensuring the total doesn't exceed available.\n    pub fn apply(self: Constraint, available: u16) u16 {\n        return switch (self) {\n            .length => |n| n,\n            .min => |n| n,\n            .max => |n| @min(n, available),\n            .ratio => |r| blk: {\n                if (r.den == 0) break :blk 0;\n                const result = (@as(u32, available) * @as(u32, r.num)) / @as(u32, r.den);\n                break :blk @intCast(@min(result, available));\n            },\n            .flex => available,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Check if two constraints are equal.\n    pub fn eql(self: Constraint, other: Constraint) bool {\n        return switch (self) {\n            .length => |n| other == .length and other.length == n,\n            .min => |n| other == .min and other.min == n,\n            .max => |n| other == .max and other.max == n,\n            .ratio => |r| other == .ratio and other.ratio.num == r.num and other.ratio.den == r.den,\n            .flex => |n| other == .flex and other.flex == n,\n        };\n    }\n};\n\n// ============================================================\n// SANITY TESTS - Basic functionality\n// ============================================================\n\ntest \"sanity: Constraint.len creates correct constraint\" {\n    const c = Constraint.len(10);\n    try std.testing.expect(c == .length);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 10), c.length);\n}\n\ntest \"sanity: Constraint.minSize creates correct constraint\" {\n    const c = Constraint.minSize(20);\n    try std.testing.expect(c == .min);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 20), c.min);\n}\n\ntest \"sanity: Constraint.maxSize creates correct constraint\" {\n    const c = Constraint.maxSize(30);\n    try std.testing.expect(c == .max);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 30), c.max);\n}\n\ntest \"sanity: Constraint.fractional creates correct constraint\" {\n    const c = Constraint.fractional(1, 3);\n    try std.testing.expect(c == .ratio);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 1), c.ratio.num);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 3), c.ratio.den);\n}\n\ntest \"sanity: Constraint.flexible creates correct constraint\" {\n    const c = Constraint.flexible(2);\n    try std.testing.expect(c == .flex);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 2), c.flex);\n}\n\ntest \"sanity: Direction enum values\" {\n    try std.testing.expect(@intFromEnum(Direction.horizontal) != @intFromEnum(Direction.vertical));\n}\n\n// ============================================================\n// BEHAVIOR TESTS - Constraint application\n// ============================================================\n\ntest \"behavior: Constraint length apply returns exact size\" {\n    const c = Constraint.len(50);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 50), c.apply(100));\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 50), c.apply(30));\n}\n\ntest \"behavior: Constraint min apply returns minimum size\" {\n    const c = Constraint.minSize(30);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 30), c.apply(100));\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 30), c.apply(20));\n}\n\ntest \"behavior: Constraint max apply caps at available\" {\n    const c = Constraint.maxSize(50);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 50), c.apply(100));\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 30), c.apply(30));\n}\n\ntest \"behavior: Constraint ratio apply calculates fraction\" {\n    const c = Constraint.fractional(1, 4);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 25), c.apply(100));\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 50),
